@cmeisl  about running in parallel is a bit more complex
We are using a remote signer and running a VC connected to several CLs, but the VC only uses the first (primary) CL. In case the primary CL goes down, the VC will connect to the second CL (bakup) and if this also fails, the new CL will connect to the third and last backup CL. In those cases the pubkey wolud be register in several CL.
Note Web3signer avoid slashing situations. So in this particular case, we can see in VC logs a connection problem between VC and the primary CL and the backup CL, so the same pubkey was registered in almost two CLs, the primary and the second backup CL. 

Regarding this particular problem, with mev-boost working fine, machine resources at good state,  and with the evidence evidence of a one-time network problem (VC logs), it may not be possible to avoid the missed proposal, since it was initiated when the network problem occurred.

@StefanBratanov  I will try to add to this thread to Lighthouse team, perhaps they can add more information about` Jan 04 15:13:19.481 ERRO Unable to publish proposer preparation to all beacon nodes`
